President Cyril Ramaphosa will address the nation on Sunday JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa is set to address the nation on COVID-19 developments at 8pm on Tuesday. There's been a steady decline in the number of coronavirus cases countrywide over the past few weeks. Vaccinations have also picked up. Scientists and health professionals have been calling for a complete end to the COVID-19 lockdown and for the national state of disaster to be lifted. eNCA reporter Heidi Giokos is covering this for us. #DStv403